Good. pool_finalise already uses `p += wh` correctly. The bug is only in pool_sweep. Let me fix it now and build.

```json
{
  "analysis": "pool_finalise uses `p += wh` correctly. The bug is only in pool_sweep's final `p += Whsize_hd(hd)` which should be `p += wh`. All pool blocks are aligned to `wh` words, but Whsize_hd computes Wosize+1 which doesn't account for sizeclass rounding. The fix is a single line change.",
  "plan": "1) Fix the bug with sed. 2) Verify the change. 3) Configure and build the compiler. 4) Run the basic test suite.",
  "commands": [
    {"keystrokes": "sed -n '650,656p' /app/ocaml/runtime/shared_heap.c\n", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "sed -i 's/      p += Whsize_hd(hd);/      p += wh;/' /app/ocaml/runtime/shared_heap.c\n", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "sed -n '648,658p' /app/ocaml/runtime/shared_heap.c\n", "duration": 0.1}
  ]
}
```
